additional_information: PCOS or Polycystic Ovary Syndrome is a hormonal condition that women can get once they start having their period cycle. It is also called as PCOD. One might be more likely to have PCOS if one's sister or mother also has it. It could also be related to problems that make your body produce too much insulin.
diagnosis: You are less likely to have PCOS
general_advice: Prevention is better than cure. Maintain a healthy weight|remain active|limit carbohydrates|take plenty of fibre in your diet
